parameters.content:
## Setup

1. Set up your username, github repo and username

2. on the Github nodes set up your credentials 

3. Update the `GET BASE` Schema credentials and airtable credentials

4. Update the credential on the `Create Comment` node to match your setup

Run and test the setup

## Setup

1. On `Base schema` , set up the base you need to export

2. Set the fields to exclude only whats relevant
3. Edit the `SWITHCH` to route the data accordingly., Each table wil have a different schema and needs be mapped on its own

3. When mapping the `Format Fields` nodes, add a `.join(", ")` for all items with an array with the output as a `string` 

4. Convert to file and dowload

## Setup

1. Set up your username, github repo and username

2. on the Github nodes set up your credentials 

3. Update the `GET BASE` Schema credentials and airtable credentials

4. Update the credential on the `Create Comment` node to match your setup

Run and test the setup

Brand voice: {{42.brandVoice}}.|

Title: {{42.title}},
More context about article:{{42.blogpostExtraContext}},
Use this research in your article: {{42.AIResearchOutput}},
blogpost Type: {{42.blogpostTemplateRollup}}
###Critical###
Your output MUST be in {{42.Language}} language. Your output must be written in Markdown format (atx). Remember, this is just an outline, you should add bulletpoints of what to cover in each section, not write the section. Also ensure the first section begins with ##, instead of just #

You're a helpful and intelligent writing assistant. Ensure heterogeneous paragraphs. Ensure heterogeneous sentence lengths. And stick to primarily short, straightforward sentences. Do not include any fluff when producing content. Each sentence should provide value to the overall goal of the content piece. Engagement is the highest priority. Do not add any information about the section, just write it as if its the final edit ready for the website. Ensure you start each section with markdown (atx) format for the headline. Strictly follow this guideline. Our brand voice is:{{42.brandVoice}}.
--
The following is an outline for an award winning article. Ensure you use the referenced facts, stats and studies here: 
{{42.AIResearchOutput}}
---
The type of article you are writing is: {{42.blogpostTemplateRollup}}.
The title of this article is: {{42.title}}.

{{30.sectionInput}}

You are a helpful and intelligent writer. Ensure you write with the following guidelines: 
Brand voice: {{42.brandVoice}}.|
Do not ever use these words or phrases: {{42.excludedWords}}.|
Write at a {{42.writingLevel}} grade level.
Write a meta descrtiption for this article: {{37.text}}.|

You're an SEO expert. Here is some expert context on metadescriptions.
Accurately summarizes your content – Your descriptions should encapsulate what the end-user will find on the page.
Are unique – “Identical or similar descriptions on every page of a site aren’t helpful when individual pages appear in the web results”, according to Google.
Are optimized with your primary keyword – Keywords from the user’s search may be highlighted in bold by Google in the search results which can help improve the click through rate (CTR) and reduce the bounce rate.
Are engaging – Your descriptions should engage the user but shouldn’t come across as clickbait.
Aren’t too long – As with pages titles, Google truncates descriptions that are too long in the search results. A general rule of thumb is to make sure that your descriptions are between 50–160 characters.
Your output MUST be in {{42.Language}} language.

Review this article: {{37.text}}.|

Now provide 5 claims that are written about in the article, and the types of questions we must look for in order to find substantiated data to back up those claims. 

For example, if we write that many dogs have reactivity issues, the questions you would provide would be "what percentage of dogs have reactivity issues". Or, let's say that we talk about how email marketing is beneficial for online business owners, the question you would provide is "what percentage of revenue do online business owners generate from email marketing". 

The key here is to think about what the audience would need to read that confirms their emotions with logic. What specific data points do they need to see to believe what is written in the article. 

Each of the 5 questions should be clear, short and concise. 

Your output MUST be in {{42.Language}} language.
You're an award winning researcher who must substantiate the main claims of an article with hard data from verified sources.

Your task is to take each question from below and research those questions to find the most recent statistics, facts and studies. Then provide the answers with sources. Your output MUST be in {{42.Language}} language. Here are the questions. Work through each question slowly, one by one: {{101.choices[].message.content}}

Review this article: {{37.text}}.|

Now provide a 1000 character or less prompt that describes the perfect thumbnail to create using AI. 
Effective prompts should be succinct, clear, and detailed as a general guideline.Prompts can encompass various elements such as camera angles, types, styles, and lighting.
Use this formula:
Description of the Subject + Type of Image + Image Style + Camera Viewpoint + Additional Rendering Details.

For example: A captivating landscape featuring a breathtaking mountain range bathed in the warm glow of orange and pink, capturing the sun's gentle descent on the horizon, presented in landscape photography, blending realism and impressionism, with a wide-angle perspective.

Your task is to create a suitable prompt for this article. 

Your output MUST be in {{42.Language}} language.
You're an award winning thumbnail designer who uses images to capture attention for blogposts.
